<h1>Problem 1068 - 2022 BMO2, P3 of 4</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>The cards from \(n\) identical decks of cards are put into boxes. Each deck contains \(50\) cards, labelled from \(1\) to \(50\). Each box can contain at most \(2022\) cards. A pile of boxes is said to be <i>regular</i> if that pile contains equal numbers of cards with each label. Show that there exists some \(N\) such that, if \(n\ge N\), then the boxes can be divided into two non-empty regular piles.</p>
